    // Let's re-evaluate.
    // To get to Box 1, we need a negative number with magnitude >= 1.
    // This means (A+B) must be odd.
    // And we need to be able to make the magnitude >= 1.
    // The only way to guarantee magnitude >= 1 is if we have at least one toy from Box 1 or Box 4.
    // If A=0 and D=0, then all initial toys have magnitude < 1.
    // The product of any number of toys with magnitude < 1 will always have magnitude < 1.
    // So, if A=0 and D=0, we can never get a toy in Box 1 (or Box 4).
    if (A == 0 && D == 0) {
        return false;
    }

    // So, (A+B) must be odd AND (A > 0 or D > 0).
    // This condition is sufficient.
    // If A > 0: We have a toy x_A <= -1.
    // If D > 0: We have a toy x_D >= 1.
