        //
        // Is N(2) always >= N(3)?
        // Yes, because for any integer K, floor(K/2) >= floor(K/3).
        // And the difference function f(K) = floor(K/x) - floor((K-1)/x) is non-decreasing.
        //
        // So, 2 will always have a count greater than or equal to any other integer k > 2.
